          <h4>What I Learned</h4>
          <p>I have been working on interactive 2-d physics simulation in the browser by writing a pure-Javascript physics 
          engine from scratch. I learned here numerical integration methods, rigid body dynamics, constrained dynamics 
          collision detection/response and the tradeoffs involved like accuracy vs. performance.
	
				This should be interesting to people developing games or other simulation apps for the web.</p>
